"1043","[IMAGE]                                                        [WELL FARGO LOGO]"
"1044","                          IMPORTANT PROXY INFORMATION"
"1045","YOUR VOTE IS IMPORTANT"
"1046","The enclosed document is a combined prospectus/proxy statement with proposals"
"1047","that pertain to the merger of certain Wells Fargo Advantage Funds(R). As a"
"1048","shareholder of one or more of the Funds, you are being asked to approve the"
"1049","merger of these Fund(s)."
"1050","THE VOTING PROCESS WILL ONLY TAKE A FEW MINUTES"
"1051","Instructions for returning your proxy are enclosed. PLEASE BE SURE TO RESPOND BY"
"1052","JUNE 8, 2010, regardless of the number of shares you own."
"1053","HIGHLIGHTS OF PROXY PROPOSALS"
"1054","For your convenience, the following information highlights the principal aspects"
"1055","of the proposals in the proxy. Full details are provided in the prospectus/proxy"
"1056","statement. We encourage you to read it carefully."
"1057","WHY HAVE WE PROPOSED THESE MERGERS?"
"1058","The enclosed prospectus/proxy statement for the merger of your funds is part of"
"1059","the pending proposal to combine the fund lineups of the Wells Fargo Advantage"
"1060","Funds and the Evergreen Funds under the Wells Fargo Advantage Funds name."
"1061","Coinciding with this proposal, Wells Fargo Funds Management, LLC, has"
"1062","recommended the merger of certain Wells Fargo Advantage Funds."
"1063","WHAT AM I BEING ASKED TO VOTE ON?"
"1064","As a shareholder of the merging (Target) fund, you are being asked to approve"
"1065","the merger of your fund into a surviving (Acquiring) fund. Your Fund's Board of"
"1066","Trustees believes that the merger is in the best interests of your Fund and that"
"1067","the interests of existing shareholders would not be diluted as a result of the"
"1068","merger. As such, they also recommend that you vote to approve it."
"1069","Upon approval by shareholders, as well as the satisfaction of other closing"
"1070","conditions, the target fund will transfer all of its assets to the acquiring"
"1071","fund, and the acquiring fund will assume all of the liabilities of the target"
"1072","fund in exchange for shares of a comparable class of the acquiring fund. The"
"1073","acquiring fund shares that you receive in a merger will have a total dollar"
"1074","value equal to that of the target fund shares that you hold at the time of the"
"1075","merger."
"1076","Each merging fund and its corresponding acquiring fund are listed below:"
"1077","<TABLE>"
"1078","<CAPTION>"
"1079","MERGING (TARGET) FUND                                         SURVIVING (ACQUIRING) FUND"
"1080","---------------------------------------------------  -----------------------------------------------"
"1081","<S>                                                  <C>"
"1082","Wells Fargo Advantage Growth Equity Fund             Wells Fargo Advantage Diversified Equity Fund"
"1083","Wells Fargo Advantage Large Cap                      Wells Fargo Advantage Capital Growth Fund"
"1084","Appreciation Fund"
"1085","Wells Fargo Advantage Stable Income Fund             Wells Fargo Advantage Ultra Short-Term"
"1086","                                                     Income Fund"
"1087","Wells Fargo Advantage Aggressive                     Wells Fargo Advantage Growth Balanced Fund"
"1088","Allocation Fund"
"1089","Wells Fargo Advantage Strategic Income Fund          Wells Fargo Advantage High Income Fund"
"1090","</TABLE>"
"1091","                                                      Continued on inside cover."
"1092","<PAGE>"
"1093","WHY HAS MY FUND'S BOARD OF TRUSTEES RECOMMENDED THAT I VOTE IN FAVOR OF"
"1094","APPROVING A MERGER?"
"1095","AMONG THE FACTORS THE BOARD CONSIDERED IN RECOMMENDING THE MERGERS WERE THE"
"1096","FOLLOWING:"
"1097","      -     Similarities and differences between the target funds' and the"
"1098","            acquiring funds' investment goals, principal investment strategies,"
"1099","            and specific portfolio characteristics, as well as the relative"
"1100","            sizes, performance records, and expenses of the funds."
"1101","      -     Shareholders will not bear any direct expenses in connection with"
"1102","            the mergers."
"1103","      -     The mergers are expected to be a nontaxable event for U.S. federal"
"1104","            income tax purposes."
"1105","HOW DO I VOTE MY SHARES?"
"1106","YOU CAN VOTE YOUR SHARES IN ONE OF FOUR WAYS:"
"1107","      1.    Vote online at the Web site address listed on your proxy card."
"1108","      2.    Call the toll-free number printed on your proxy card."
"1109","      3.    Complete and sign the enclosed proxy card and return by mail in the"
"1110","            enclosed postage-paid return envelope (if mailed in the United"
"1111","            States)."
"1112","      4.    Attend the special meeting scheduled to be held on June 8, 2010."
"1113","            Whether or not you expect to attend the meeting, we encourage you to"
"1114","            vote online or by phone or mail."
"1115","WHAT IS THE DUE DATE FOR RETURNING MY VOTE?"
"1116","Please read the enclosed proxy materials, carefully consider the information"
"1117","provided, and then vote promptly. The voting process only takes a few minutes. A"
"1118","final vote will take place at a special meeting of shareholders scheduled for"
"1119","June 8, 2010. Your vote must be received by that date."
"1120","IS THIS A TAXABLE EVENT FOR SHAREHOLDERS?"
"1121","NO. Each merger is expected to be a nontaxable event for U.S. federal income tax"
"1122","purposes."
"1123","WHOM SHOULD I CALL WITH QUESTIONS ABOUT THE VOTING PROCESS?"
"1124","If you have any questions about any proposal or related proxy materials, please"
"1125","call your investment professional, trust officer, or a Wells Fargo Advantage"
"1126","Funds client service representative at 1-800-222-8222, 24 hours a day, 7 days a"
"1127","week. If you have any questions about the voting process, or if you would like"
"1128","to vote by telephone, you may call our proxy solicitor, the Altman Group Inc.,"
"1129","at 1-800-499-8519."
