"1462","On December 31, 2008, the parent company of the investment adviser to the"
"1463","Evergreen funds, Wachovia Corporation (Wachovia), and the parent company of"
"1464","the investment adviser to Wells Fargo Advantage Funds(R), Wells Fargo & Company"
"1465","(Wells Fargo), merged. Since that date, the investment adviser to the"
"1466","Evergreen funds, Evergreen Investment Management Company, LLC (EIMC), and the"
"1467","investment adviser to Wells Fargo Advantage Funds, Wells Fargo Funds Management,"
"1468","LLC (Funds Management), have considered rationalizing and reorganizing their"
"1469","mutual fund businesses. After multiple presentations to and discussions with the"
"1470","Boards of Trustees of both the Evergreen funds and Wells Fargo Advantage Funds"
"1471","regarding these matters, on December 30, 2009, EIMC proposed to the Boards of"
"1472","Trustees of the Evergreen funds, and on January 11, 2010, Funds Management"
"1473","proposed to the Boards of Trustees of Wells Fargo Advantage Funds, the mergers"
"1474","outlined in the table below. Both the Boards of Trustees of the Evergreen funds"
"1475","and Wells Fargo Advantage Funds approved the proposed mergers and the related"
"1476","Agreement and Plan of Reorganization, subject to the approval by shareholders of"
"1477","each Target Fund (shown in the table below), as part of a comprehensive set of"
"1478","mutual fund mergers across the two fund families."
